OL,3,C'Died fighting for answers': Tributes
OL,4,Cpaid to father of Chinook crash victim
OL,6,FThe father of one of the victims of
OL,7,Fthe 1994 Chinook crash on the Mull of
OL,8,FKintyre has died aged 96, with
OL,9,Fcampaigners saying he died "fighting
OL,10,Ffor answers".
OL,12,FJohn Dockerty's son, Major Christopher
OL,13,FDockerty, was one of the 29 killed
OL,14,Fwhen RAF Chinook ZD576 crashed in
OL,15,Ffoggy weather while flying from RAF
OL,16,FAldergrove, in Northern Ireland, to
OL,17,FFort George, near Inverness.
OL,19,FThe incident was initially blamed on
OL,20,Fpilot error before this was overturned
OL,21,Fin 2011.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/7
